How Power Press Operates?<br/><br/>A power press is a machine which converts metals into miraculous shapes. Various products like brackets, frame pieces, electronic enclosures etc., can be manufactured using a power press. There are many different types of power press machines like &lt;a title=&quot;C type power press&quot; href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhavyamachinetools.com%2Fsheet-metal-machine%2Fpower-press%2Fc-type.html"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.bhavyamachinetools.com/sheet-metal-machine/power-press/c-type.html</a>]C type power press[/url] and pillar type power press which can be further classified into mechanical power press and hydraulic power press. Due to the advancement in technology, the power press has also undergone many changes. One of the most popular power press available today is the CNC power press having PC based controllers. But, the most commonly used power press is the &lt;a title=&quot;mechanical power press&quot; href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhavyamachinetools.com%2Fsheet-metal-machine%2Fpower-press%2Fc-type.html"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.bhavyamachinetools.com/sheet-metal-machine/power-press/c-type.html</a>]mechanical power press[/url] which includes a moving ram used shape as well as bend metals and a stationery bed or surface where the material to be shaped can be placed. The power press punches the material, forms the material, bends the material, shapes the material using combination of different dies attached to the moving ram and bed. To transmit power into the press, clutch is used. The clutches remain engaged until the power press completes the full cycle. High accuracy in bending and shaping metals is provided by a power press. Besides the above working of a power press, you also need to have information about the basic setup procedure required for a power press as given below:-
<br />&lt;ul&gt;
<br />&lt;li&gt;The basic thing to be considered is the material thickness and the output expected. You need to review the drawing which specifies the type, dimensions and the angles required. This is very much important to determine the type of tooling and dies to be utilized in a power press.&lt;/li&gt;
<br />&lt;li&gt;The tonnage should be determined which depends on the bending method.&lt;/li&gt;
<br />&lt;li&gt;There should be accuracy in the positioning in tooling which is very important to achieve accuracy in the output.&lt;/li&gt;
<br /><br />&lt;li&gt;The parameters should be adjusted depending on the job to be completed. However, this requires trained and efficient operators. But, with the advancement of the machineries, this can be done by even untrained operators too.&lt;/li&gt;
<br />&lt;li&gt;It is always recommended to do a test bend of the material in order to detect if further adjustments are to be done.&lt;/li&gt;
<br />&lt;/ul&gt;
<br />After knowing the above working of the power press and the setup process, it becomes necessary to know about the safety measures required to be taken while operating a power press. A power press if not maintained and operated properly can cause accidents which should be avoided using below mentioned safety measures.
<br />&lt;ul&gt;
<br />&lt;li&gt;The power press and its guards, control systems, ancillary equipment like automatic feed system should be maintained properly so that it doesn’t put people at risk.&lt;/li&gt;
<br />&lt;li&gt;The maintenance work on the power press should be carried out when the machine is completely switched off and should be done by people who possess right skills and knowledge.&lt;/li&gt;
<br />&lt;li&gt;Proper training should be provided to the operator responsible of operating the power press.&lt;/li&gt;
<br />&lt;li&gt;The people operating the machine, supervisors and managing the use should be made aware about the specific safety measures to be taken while using power press through written instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
<br />&lt;li&gt;The power press should be regularly and thoroughly examined by the competent person and ensured that it is sound and working in proper condition.&lt;/li&gt;
<br />&lt;li&gt;It is always recommended to keep the record of the maintenance activities performed at a power press to ensure that the power press has been properly maintained.&lt;/li&gt;
<br />&lt;/ul&gt;
<br />As far as health and safety is concerned, it becomes very much necessary to follow the above mentioned steps in a workshop using a power press. The purpose of thorough examination and test of a &lt;a title=&quot;power press machine&quot; href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhavyamachinetools.com%2Fsheet-metal-machine%2Fpower-press%2Fc-type.html"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.bhavyamachinetools.com/sheet-metal-machine/power-press/c-type.html</a>]power press machine[/url] before operating is to determine whether the power press and its parts have been installed properly, whether it is safe to operate and whether there are any defects which could make a power press unsafe to operate. Moreover, the law requires that the power press installed in your workshop is maintained properly which will also includes that your employees operating or maintaining power press have adequate knowledge and skills required to complete the job.

Significance of Lathe Machine for Metal Shaping Industries<br/><br/>There is no doubt in saying that necessity is the mother of all inventions. All the machines are invented with a single purpose and that is to reduce labour work and get things done quickly. In ancient times, giving shapes to metal was a tedious job and time consuming process. The invention of lathe machine made the job of metal shaping much easier. Basically, a lathe machine is used to remove the unwanted part from the metals to give it a new shape. The material is rotated against the tool which trims down the material into shape. In olden times, lathe machine was operated manually but the machine got many innovative improvements after that. The technological changes brought many versatile changes to a lathe machine. There are many products which we use in our daily life using metals of different shapes and sizes. The production of all these products has been possible only due to a lathe machine. Every other industry is influenced by the lathe machine as it can even perform the complicated process of shaping metals. To manufacture any metal product, the basic requirement is to shape it and that is possible only due to a lathe machine.
<br />Elements of a Lathe Machine
<br />Generally, a lathe machine provides a variety of rotating speeds and different features which can enable manual and automatic controls for moving the cutting tool. There are various &lt;a title=&quot;types of lathe machines&quot; href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhavyamachinetools.com%2Flathe-machine.html"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.bhavyamachinetools.com/lathe-machine.html</a>]types of lathe machines[/url] available like light duty lathe machine, medium duty lathe machine, heavy duty lathe machine, extra heavy duty lathe machine etc. No matter which lathe machine you choose, suiting to your job requirements, below are the common elements which are present in every lathe machine as given below:-
<br />Chuck – is used to hold the work piece and can be replaced with Jacobs chuck or centre for alternative work holding.
<br />Tailstock – is used to hold and located the tail centre and can be unlocked and slid towards the chuck.
<br />[Tail centre– is used to hold the end of long pieces of work, as the small lengths can just be held in the chuck. Centre can be removed and replaced with Jacobs chuck and drill and the advance wheel rotated to drill the work.
<br />Tool Post – is used to hold the cutting tool in a precise location.
<br />Cross Slide– it runs on the bed rails and has a mounting for the tool post which can be driven forward by the tool post advance wheel to bring the cutting tool on to the work peice.&lt;/p&gt;
<br />Cross Slide Advance[/b] – It is used to move the cross slide and tool post sideways and hence the cutting tool towards and away from the chuck.
<br />Drive pulleys and belts– are used to achieve various speeds by varying the belt position on the pulleys.
